cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about face hallucination using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves optimizing tasks and proposing a new network architecture, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper deals with image processing and manipulation, which could also place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves face alignment and pose estimation, which could potentially place it under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
